    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the Greek style of sculpture produced by Athenian sculptor Skopas during the 4th century BCE and characterized by vigorous action and the depiction of emotion seen especially in the deep set eyes and upturned gaze of the face.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de escultura griego producido por el escultor ateniense Skopas durante el siglo IV a.C y que se caracteriza por la acción vigorosa y la representación de emoción vistas sobre todo en los ojos fijos profundos y la mirada hacia arriba de la cara.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de Griekse stijl in de beeldhouwkunst van de Atheense beeldhouwer Skopas, in de 4de eeuw v. Chr. De stijl kenmerkt zich door krachtige actie en de weergave van emoties, vooral zichtbaar in de diep liggende ogen en de opgerichte blik van de gezichten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱於西元前四世紀間，由雅典的雕刻家斯科帕斯（Skopas）所創作的希臘雕塑風格，此風格特徵為強而有力的姿態動作與情感的描繪，尤其是深邃的雙眼及向上仰望凝視的臉部。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
